Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{1}(chopped into 2cm chunks) into 2cm chunks
(no need to peel) and pop on a large lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then arrange in a single layer and roast on the top shelf
of your oven until starting to colour, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Meanwhile, half, peel and finely slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Pick the @sage{1}(finely chopped)
leaves from their stalks and finely chop (discard the stalks). Roughly chop the @hazelnuts{25}.
Trim the @brussels sprouts{200} then chop in half and pop on another large lined baking tray.
Drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat, spread out, then set aside -
we will roast them later.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add the shallot. Cook, stirring,
until soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the hazelnuts, @dried cranberries{30} and half the sage.
Remove from the heat and tip the stuffing into a #mixing bowl{}. Season to taste with a pinch
of salt and pepper. Cover with #foil{} to keep warm and set to one side.

Return the frying pan to medium-high heat. Add a splash of oil. Once hot, place the
@british turkey steaks{2} in the pan and fry until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes} each side.
Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to the tray with the sweet potato (keep the frying pan!)
and pop the tray onto the middle shelf of your oven. Roast until cooked, ~{10-15%minutes}.
At the same time, roast the sprouts on the top shelf until tender and crispy, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Return the now empty frying pan to medium-high heat. Pour in the @white wine vinegar{12}.
Stir well, scraping the pan with a #wooden spoon{} to get all the tasty bits left behind by
the turkey! Add the @water{250} (for the gravy), @chicken stock powder{1} and
@redcurrant jelly{25} and stir to dissolve. Simmer and reduce until you have a slightly
thickened sauce, ~{5%minutes}. Add the remaining sage and season to taste with salt and
pepper.

Once everything is cooked, stir the brussels sprouts and sweet potato into the bowl with the
rest of the stuffing. Place the turkey steaks on a #chopping board{} and thinly slice.
Dived the stuffing between your plates with the turkey slices on top. Spoon over the sagey
pan-sauce. Tuck in!